= ON THE REPORT OF SIGHTING OF UNIDENTIFIED FLYING OBJECT

On the night of 12 October 1972, at approximately 23:15 CET, a Lufthansa cargo flight (LH-402) en route from Frankfurt to Munich reported sustained proximity to an unidentified luminous object.

​Altitude: 28,000 feet.

​Visual Characteristics: A spherical, self-luminous body, approximately 1.5 meters in diameter. Emitance: Pulsating amber-to-white light.
​
Kinematics: The object maintained a "velcro-position" exactly 50 meters off the starboard wingtip. Radar telemetry from civilian ATC showed no signature, yet military ELINT (Electronic Intelligence) stations in the Bavarian Forest recorded localized electromagnetic interference consistent with high-frequency ionization.

> ​"The object did not behave like a drone or a conventional flare. It mirrored our evasive maneuvers with zero inertia. When I throttled up, it maintained distance. When I banked hard left, it remained fixed relative to our wing as if mechanically attached by an invisible tether. There was no visible propulsion system, no heat shimmer, and no exhaust."

Signed, <br>
Dr. Hanswoger

